Sentece: The areas under the plasma concentration versus time curve (AUC) of the thiolactone intermediates in the portal vein plasma after an oral dose of prasugrel (1 mg kg(-1)) and clopidogrel (0.77 mg kg(-1)) were 15.8 +/- 15.9 ng h ml(-1) and 0.113 +/- 0.226 ng h ml(-1), respectively, in rats, and 454 +/- 104 ng h ml(-1) and 23.3 +/- 4.3 ng h ml(-1), respectively, in dogs, indicating efficient hydrolysis of prasugrel and little metabolism of clopidogrel to their thiolactones in the intestine.
